**Defines TypeScript interfaces and type aliases for the npx-driven installer workflow that copies ARE commands and hooks to AI runtime configuration directories.**

## Exported Types

**`Runtime`** — String literal union `'claude' | 'opencode' | 'gemini' | 'all'` specifying target AI assistant runtime for installation.

**`Location`** — String literal union `'global' | 'local'` distinguishing user-level installations (`~/.claude`, `~/.config/opencode`, `~/.gemini`) from project-level installations (`.claude`, `.opencode`, `.gemini`).

**`InstallerArgs`** — Interface for parsed command-line arguments supporting both interactive prompts and non-interactive flag mode:
- `runtime?: Runtime` — Target runtime or `'all'` for multi-runtime installation
- `global: boolean` — Install to user-level configuration directory
- `local: boolean` — Install to project-level configuration directory
- `uninstall: boolean` — Uninstall instead of install
- `force: boolean` — Overwrite existing files without prompting
- `help: boolean` — Display help message and exit
- `quiet: boolean` — Suppress banner and informational output

**`InstallerResult`** — Interface capturing outcome of single runtime/location installation operation:
- `success: boolean` — Overall operation success indicator
- `runtime: Exclude<Runtime, 'all'>` — Installed runtime (excludes synthetic `'all'` union member)
- `location: Location` — Installation target location
- `filesCreated: string[]` — Absolute paths of successfully written files
- `filesSkipped: string[]` — Paths skipped due to existing files when `force: false`
- `errors: string[]` — Error messages from failed operations
- `hookRegistered?: boolean` — Claude-specific flag indicating `settings.json` hook registration success
- `versionWritten?: boolean` — Flag indicating VERSION file creation for update check system

**`RuntimePaths`** — Interface defining resolved filesystem paths for runtime installation targets:
- `global: string` — User-level configuration directory (e.g., `~/.claude`)
- `local: string` — Project-level configuration directory (e.g., `.claude`)
- `settingsFile: string` — Path to runtime's settings file for hook registration (e.g., `~/.claude/settings.json`)

## Type Constraints

`InstallerResult.runtime` uses `Exclude<Runtime, 'all'>` to ensure result objects reference concrete runtimes (`'claude'`, `'opencode'`, `'gemini'`) rather than the synthetic `'all'` selector used in `InstallerArgs.runtime`.

## Integration Points

Consumed by:
- `src/installer/prompts.ts` — Interactive CLI prompts for runtime/location selection
- `src/installer/operations.ts` — File copying, hook registration, VERSION file writing
- `src/installer/paths.ts` — Runtime path resolution with environment variable overrides
- `src/installer/uninstall.ts` — Removal of installed files and hook deregistration